definitions.820-3330: What is 820-3330? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.

threads.title: [SOLVED]<LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3330</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> only one usb working
threads.message:
I've got this <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3330</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> board and only one of the usb ports work properly. USB A is not working, it does power on the light on my external drive but that is about it. i guess this port is also a SMC DEBUG port. i get 3.3v on pin 2 of L4600 which makes me think it might be in DEBUG mode, but not to sure. i get nothing on pin 1-2 of <CHIP>U4650</CHIP>. not sure where to go next on this. i watch a video from louis but it was a diff issue. found a few people have had this issue, but no solutions yet.

any help would be awesome.

threads.title: [SOLVED]<LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3330</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> only one usb working
threads.message:
If you get 3.3v on pin 2 of L4600 you should get 3.3v on pin 1 of L4600 and 3.3v at pin 1 of <CHIP>U4650</CHIP>.

First check again continuity at L4600 between pin 1-2 and between pins 3-4
Then trace continuity and compare diode mode values.
Clamp Diode <DIODE>D4600</DIODE> can be shorted also.

You are in debug mode only if Select pin 10 of <CHIP>U4650</CHIP> is low.

threads.title: [SOLVED]<LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3330</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> only one usb working
threads.message:
i check and did not have continuity between pin 1-2 of L4600. replaced L4600 and all is working as it should.

Thanks. Maybe next time ill turn my brain on before working on boards. :)

mark as solved
